So who really pays....  The working middle class.  What has the carbon tax really done?  It is a SIGNIFICANT contributor to inflation and the high cost of living particularly in BC. As part of that those who can now burn wood and/or garbage for fuel sources.  These are "unofficial" CO2 sources so the "official" consumption has gone down, but at best the actual CO2 production is the same or more considering burning wood or garbage for fuel is very inefficient. Then, 1st pair's escaping A won't annihilate with its B (which fell into the BH), but with neighbouring's pair escaping B.
